This paper deals with the problem of symbolic association of object-word mappings, which is a topic of interest in natural language processing and machine learning. The paper proposes a method for handling missing elements in multimodal sequences using Long Short-Term Memories (LSTMs) and Dynamic Time Warping (DTW). This work is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including computational linguistics (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
